.Dd $Mdocdate: May 31 2007 $
.Dt RESETTODR 9
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm resettodr
.Nd set battery-backed clock from system time
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Ft void
.Fn resettodr "void"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn resettodr
function sets the system's battery backed clock based on the contents
of the system
.Va time_second
variable or a function such as
.Xr microtime 9 .
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr inittodr 9 ,
.Xr microtime 9 ,
.Xr time_second 9
@


1.6
log
@convert to new .Dd format;
@
text
@d1 1
a1 1
.\"	$OpenBSD: resettodr.9,v 1.5 2000/10/12 18:06:02 aaron Exp $
d33 1
a33 1
.Dd $Mdocdate$
d47 3
a49 2
.Va time
variable.
d52 2
a53 9
.Xr time 9
.Sh BUGS
On many systems,
.Fn resettodr
has to convert from
.Va time
to a time expressed in terms of year, month, day, hours, minutes,
and seconds.
Many of the implementations could share code, but do not.
@


